  section
    h2 DOM
    h5 Document Object Model
    ul
      li Programming interface for HTML, XML, and SVG documents (Handlers too)
      li The DOM is what the browser renders
    p.fragment.fade-in.
      Basically a Tree of Nodes for you to play with through JS that the browser renders with your assets

  section
    h2 Shadow DOM
    p.
      The Shadow DOM is a browser feature, in which it can include a subtree to
      the rendering part, but you won't see it in the main DOM.
    p.
      Cases in point
    ul
      li <code>&lt;input id="foo" type="range"></code>
      li <code>&lt;video src="kool-aid-oh-yeah.mp4" autoplay controls>&lt;/video></code>
      li <code>&lt;audio src="kumbaya.mp3">&lt;/audio></code>
      li <code>&lt;a href="www.thetwilightzone.com">Link&lt;a></code>

  section
    h2 Polymer
    p.
      Polymer uses the Shadow DOM to allow you to create your own Custom HTML Component,
      and allow the user of that component to use it as follows:
    pre(style="width:100%; font-size: 0.40em;")
      code(style="max-height: 600px;").hljs.html.
        &lt;claudios-fabulous-swagifier>
          &lt;user>John Doe&lt;/user>
          &lt;birthdate>2000&lt;/birthdate>
          &lt;bio>I have no swag because I'm too young to know better&lt;/bio>
        &lt;/claudios-fabulous-swagifier>

  section
